Aim
To perform a basic Nmap port scan on a target website and identify open ports and running services.
Introduction
Nmap (Network Mapper) is a network scanning and security auditing tool used to discover hosts, open ports,
and services running on a target system. Port scanning helps identify accessible network services and analyze
the security status of a target machine.
Nmap is widely used in cybersecurity, penetration testing, and network administration.
Procedure
Step 1: Install Nmap
Open Kali Linux terminal and install Nmap:
sudo apt install nmap -y
Step 2: Verify Installation
Check whether Nmap is installed successfully:
nmap --version
Step 3: Perform Basic Port Scan
Run the following command to scan the target website:
nmap www.grace.edu.in
Step 4: Analyze the Output
Observe:
• Open ports
• Running services
• Port states
Implementation
Command Used
nmap www.grace.edu.in
Explanation
• nmap → Starts the Nmap tool
• www.grace.edu.in → Target website/domain
Output
PORT STATE SERVICE
21/tcp open ftp
80/tcp open http
443/tcp open https
3306/tcp open mysql
Analysis
Port Service
21 FTP
80 HTTP
443 HTTPS
